# Force LF on shell scripts regardless of `core.autocrlf`.
# CRLF line endings make bash treat `\r` as part of variables in
# command substitution, which breaks `cd "$(pwd)"` etc. with errors
# like `cd: $'/path\n/path/..': No such file or directory`.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Same story for files bash or other Unix tooling parses directly.
*.toml text eol=lf
Cargo.lock text eol=lf
rust-toolchain.toml text eol=lf

# Leave markdown / JSON / TypeScript alone — they work in either form.
# If you hit an end-of-line issue in a specific source file, add it
# here rather than flipping `core.autocrlf` globally.
